Ci.port.Q_flow.comment: Heat flow rate (positive if flowing from outside into the component)

Rea.Q_flow.comment: Heat flow rate from port_a -> port_b

Ria.Q_flow.comment: Heat flow rate from port_a -> port_b

preHeat.port.Q_flow.comment: Heat flow rate (positive if flowing from outside into the component)

preSol.port.Q_flow.comment: Heat flow rate (positive if flowing from outside into the component)

senTZone.port.Q_flow.comment: Heat flow rate (positive if flowing from outside into the component)

Aw.k.comment: Gain value multiplied with input signal

con.I.y_start.comment: Initial or guess value of output (= state)

con.Nd.comment: The higher Nd, the more ideal the derivative block

con.Ni.comment: Ni*Ti is time constant of anti-windup compensation

con.P.k.comment: Gain value multiplied with input signal

con.gainPID.k.comment: Gain value multiplied with input signal

con.gainTrack.k.comment: Gain value multiplied with input signal

con.xd_start.comment: Initial or guess value for state of derivative block

con.xi_start.comment: Initial or guess value for integrator output (= integrator state)

preHeat.alpha.comment: Temperature coefficient of heat flow rate

preSol.alpha.comment: Temperature coefficient of heat flow rate

con.I.initType.comment: Type of initialization (1: no init, 2: steady state, 3,4: initial output)

con.initType.comment: Type of initialization (1: no init, 2: steady state, 3: initial state, 4: initial output)

con.I.use_set.comment: = true, if set port enabled and used as reinitialization value when reset

con.limiter.strict.comment: = true, if strict limits with noEvent(..)

con.strict.comment: = true, if strict limits with noEvent(..)

equation: homotopy(smooth(0, if con.limiter.u > con.limiter.uMax then con.limiter.uMax else if con.limiter.u < con.limiter.uMin then con.limiter.uMin else con.limiter.u), con.limiter.u)

assert(con.limiter.uMax >= con.limiter.uMin, "Limiter: Limits must be consistent. However, uMax (=" + String(con.limiter.uMax, 6, 0, true) + ") < uMin (=" + String(con.limiter.uMin, 6, 0, true) + ")");
con.addPID.k1 * con.P.y + con.addPID.k2 * con.Dzero.k + con.addPID.k3 * con.I.y
smooth(0, if con.limiter.u > con.limiter.uMax then con.limiter.uMax else if con.limiter.u < con.limiter.uMin then con.limiter.uMin else con.limiter.u)
con.addI.k1 * Tset + con.addI.k2 * Ci.T + con.addI.k3 * con.gainTrack.y

assert(con.limiter.uMax >= con.limiter.uMin, "Limiter: Limits must be consistent. However, uMax (=" + String(con.limiter.uMax, 6, 0, true) + ") < uMin (=" + String(con.limiter.uMin, 6, 0, true) + ")");
assert(preSol.T_ref >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= preSol.T_ref, has value: " + String(preSol.T_ref, "g"));
assert(preHeat.T_ref >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= preHeat.T_ref, has value: " + String(preHeat.T_ref, "g"));

assert(con.limiter.homotopyType >= Modelica.Blocks.Types.LimiterHomotopy.NoHomotopy and con.limiter.homotopyType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.LimiterHomotopy.LowerLimit, "Variable violating min/max constraint: Modelica.Blocks.Types.LimiterHomotopy.NoHomotopy <= con.limiter.homotopyType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.LimiterHomotopy.LowerLimit, has value: " + String(con.limiter.homotopyType, "d"));
assert(con.k >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= con.k, has value: " + String(con.k, "g"));
assert(con.Ni >= 1e-13, "Variable violating min constraint: 1e-13 <= con.Ni, has value: " + String(con.Ni, "g"));

assert(con.I.initType >= Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.NoInit and con.I.initType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.InitialOutput, "Variable violating min/max constraint: Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.NoInit <= con.I.initType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.InitialOutput, has value: " + String(con.I.initType, "d"));
assert(con.Ti >= 1e-60, "Variable violating min constraint: 1e-60 <= con.Ti, has value: " + String(con.Ti, "g"));
assert(con.wp >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= con.wp, has value: " + String(con.wp, "g"));

assert(con.homotopyType >= Modelica.Blocks.Types.LimiterHomotopy.NoHomotopy and con.homotopyType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.LimiterHomotopy.LowerLimit, "Variable violating min/max constraint: Modelica.Blocks.Types.LimiterHomotopy.NoHomotopy <= con.homotopyType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.LimiterHomotopy.LowerLimit, has value: " + String(con.homotopyType, "d"));

assert(con.initType >= Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.NoInit and con.initType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.InitialOutput, "Variable violating min/max constraint: Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.NoInit <= con.initType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.Init.InitialOutput, has value: " + String(con.initType, "d"));
assert(con.Nd >= 1e-13, "Variable violating min constraint: 1e-13 <= con.Nd, has value: " + String(con.Nd, "g"));
assert(con.wd >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= con.wd, has value: " + String(con.wd, "g"));
assert(con.Td >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= con.Td, has value: " + String(con.Td, "g"));

assert(con.controllerType >= Modelica.Blocks.Types.SimpleController.P and con.controllerType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.SimpleController.PID, "Variable violating min/max constraint: Modelica.Blocks.Types.SimpleController.P <= con.controllerType <= Modelica.Blocks.Types.SimpleController.PID, has value: " + String(con.controllerType, "d"));
assert(TSetHeaOcc >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= TSetHeaOcc, has value: " + String(TSetHeaOcc, "g"));
assert(TSetHeaUno >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= TSetHeaUno, has value: " + String(TSetHeaUno, "g"));
assert(TSetCooOcc >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= TSetCooOcc, has value: " + String(TSetCooOcc, "g"));
assert(TSetCooUno >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= TSetCooUno, has value: " + String(TSetCooUno, "g"));
assert(Ci.T >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= Ci.T, has value: " + String(Ci.T, "g"));
assert(Ce.T >= 0.0, "Variable violating min constraint: 0.0 <= Ce.T, has value: " + String(Ce.T, "g"));
